Visualizing Fort Collins Public Incidents¶

The goal of this project is to visualize the Fort Collins Public Incident Log using a map and other useful visuals.
Readers will be able to gain an understanding of where most incidents occur from the map and charts, as well as what kinds of incidents are most common.

Main Tools Used:

  • Folium
  • Pandas/Numpy/MatPlotLib

In [2]:
features = ["Incident No", "Case Number", "Date/Time", "Call Type", "Location", "Call Disposition","meta_row_index", "meta_row_id", "GeoreferenceLocation"]
data = pd.read_csv('/Users/andrehochmuth/documents/cs445/ProjectFoCo/PublicIncidentLog.csv',names=features,header=0)
data = data.drop(columns=['meta_row_index','meta_row_id','Case Number','Incident No'])

#Gets rid of any data with no GeoReference Location
data = data[data.GeoreferenceLocation.notnull()]

lat = []
lon = []

# For each row in a varible,
for row in data['GeoreferenceLocation']:
    try:
        # Split the row by comma and append everything before the comma to lat
        lat.append(float(row.split('\n')[1].split(',')[0][1:]))
        # Split the row by comma and append
        # everything after the comma to lon
        lon.append(float(row.split('\n')[1].split(',')[1][:-1]))
    # But if you get an error
    except:
        # append a missing value to lat
        lat.append(np.NaN)
        # append a missing value to lon
        lon.append(np.NaN)
# Create two new columns from lat and lon
data['Latitude'] = lat
data['Longitude'] = lon
data.reset_index(inplace=True)
